name: 4-alpha-D-{(1->4)-alpha-D-glucano}trehalose trehalohydrolase
classes: Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
reaction: hydrolysis of (1->4)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkage in 4-alpha-D-[(1->4)-alpha-D-glucanosyl]n trehalose to yield trehalose and (1->4)-alpha-D-glucan [RN:R11256]

references.title: Formation of trehalose from maltooligosaccharides by a novel enzymatic system.
